CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 17, 1961, pg. 6A reads: "Gift For Potentate - Standing, left to right: Noble John W. Goggins, Deputy Imperial Promotional Director; Noble Clarence R. Queen, Illustrious Potentate; Noble Marshall S. Johnson, Imperial Captain of the Guard, and Noble William Fitzpatrick, PP, and Daughters Natalie Mucker and Fitzpatrick of Detroit's Marracci Temple, were photographed as Noble Queen received a gift, during the Potentate's Ball, recently, in Pittsburgh."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Shriners, including Mrs. William Fitzpatrick on left, William Fitzpatrick, third from left, Clarence R. Queen, fourth from left, and Natalie Mucker, second from right, posed in interior with two toned walls and ornate molding for Shriners Potentate's Ball
